description:
"Kennedy" is a news panel show hosted by Kennedy Montgomery. Kennedy Montgomery is a libertarian that you may recognize from 90's MTV, Stossel, and the Independents.

Kennedy starts the night off talking about Bernie Sander's surge. Big showings at rallys and celebrity endorsements aplenty. How the GOP candidates are handling Trump. Rand attacks, Cruz pulls punches.

Tonight's panel consists of ANDY LEVY, JIMMY FAILLA, and KAYLEIGH MCENANY. They continue to talk about trump and the way GOP candidates are dealing with his success. Bernie Sanders gains endorsement of legendary rapper Lil B THE FUCKING BASED GOD. *Cough* Excuse me.

PETE HEGSETH is here to talk about the Iranian deal and a group of veterans going by "Veterans against the deal".

Our party panel returns. They'll be talking about the founder of SPIN magazine and his tirade against modern music.

The panel is back. First up - Who is Lawrence Lessig and should he run? Afterwards they discuss Rhonda Rousey calling out Floyd Mayweather, champion of wife beaters. Then they move on to robots marrying humans.

The EPA accidentally caused a 300 million gallon toxic spill. KATHERINE MANGU-WARD and TIMOTHY SANDEFUR are here to talk about how awful they are for doing that. (Woop, sovereign immunity.)

Nightcap: F is for fat. Kids, obesity, and school diets.
